headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 30 points, 13 rebounds and eight assists to help the Milwaukee Bucks rout the Detroit Pistons 131-101 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo has 30 points, Bucks rout Pistons

events.name: New York Knicks at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Obi Toppin scored a career-high 35 points, and the New York Knicks beat the Washington Wizards 114-92 on Friday night.
— After a season full of complications, things are finally simple for the Brooklyn Nets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Nets beat Cavs, in position to take No. 7 in East

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 29 points and 12 rebounds, Gary Trent Jr. made the winning layup with 4.8 seconds left and the Toronto Raptors beat the Houston Rockets 117-115 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam helps Raptors rally to beat Rockets 117-115

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo made the go-ahead dunk with 27 seconds remaining and scored 24 points in the Miami Heat’s 113-109 comeback victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo's late dunk lifts Heat over Hawks, 113-109

headlines.description: — The Charlotte Hornets looked like they had their sights set on something bigger while the Chicago Bulls delivered their worst effort in recent memory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball scores 24, Hornets bury Bulls early in 133-117 win

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 39 points, 11 rebounds and his 16th technical foul of the season for the Dallas Mavericks, who will open the playoffs at home for the first time since 2011 after their 128-78 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has 39 points, 11 rebounds, 16th tech in Mavs' win

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 33 points and the NBA-leading Phoenix Suns overcame a 17-point deficit in the fourth quarter to beat the Utah Jazz 111-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-best Suns overcome 17-point deficit in 4th to beat Jazz

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Stanley Johnson scored a season-high 21 points and the Los Angeles Lakers snapped their eight-game losing streak with a 120-101 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers snap 8-game skid with 120-101 win over Thunder
